reviews.text:
Just like any other branches of CAN.TEEN but with a wide upper view as it's located inside the square of the center. 

Over priced and extra busy at lunch hour since it's located inside the Central Business District.

Terrific WiFi connection, the CSL network disconnect every 5 minutes.
Fast food shop in Hong Kong style. Good milk tea.
Good resonable food for the price. Pay either the cashier or use the slelf service screens (pay with octopus). Will snack here again.

Not sure why the average score here is so low. Even though this is a food court, food is decent and environment is clean. Best of all, prices are extremely reasonable especially considering it's right beside Pacific Place. I see some people complaining about the price. Are you kidding me - where else are you going to have a decent lunch for HK$50 in this neighborhood?
Nice location, average food. But then one shouldn't expect too much from a fast food chain.
